<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:lang="en" xml:id="editorial-abbrevuncert">
    <teiHeader>
        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Uncertain expansion of abbreviation</title>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt><p/></publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc><p/></sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
    </teiHeader>
    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="content">
                <div type="leiden">
                <cit type="interpretive">
                    <quote>1) α(βγ(?)), 2) α(βγ)(?)</quote>
                </cit>
                <cit type="diplomatic">
                    <quote>none</quote>
                </cit>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    1) <expan>
                        <abbr>α</abbr>
                        <ex cert="low">βγ</ex>
                    </expan>
                    
                    2) <expan cert="low">
                        <abbr>α</abbr>
                        <ex>βγ</ex>
                    </expan>
                </egXML>
                <p>The question mark (?) should be exactly linked to the expanded part, inside the brackets: in this case the <att>cert</att> attribute goes with <gi>ex</gi>;
                    if the question mark (?) is outside the brackets, it concerns the whole word and <att>cert</att> should go with <gi>expan</gi>.</p>
            </div>
            </div>
